{"id":108,"parent_id":95,"book_id":2,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":108,"title":"Acts 13","subtitle":"","short_title":"Acts","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 13"],[".studySummary",["i","Saul and Barnabas are called to missionary service—Saul, now called Paul, curses a sorcerer—Christ is a descendant of David—Paul offers the gospel to Israel, then to the Gentiles."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.1","order":"03.07.013.13259"},["b","1"],"Now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"prophets"],"and teachers; as Barnabas, and Simeon that was called Niger, and Lucius of Cyrene, and Manaen, which had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.2","order":"03.07.013.13260"},["b","2"],"As they ministered to the Lord, and",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_2a"},"fasted"],", the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_2b"},"Holy Ghost"],"said,",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_2c"},"Separate"],"me Barnabas and Saul for the work whereunto I have",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_2d"},"called"],"them."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.3","order":"03.07.013.13261"},["b","3"],"And when they had fasted and prayed, and",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"laid"],["i","their"],["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_3b"},"hands"],"on them, they sent",["i","them"],"away."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.4","order":"03.07.013.13262"},["b","4"],"¶So they, being sent forth by the Holy Ghost, departed unto Seleucia; and from thence they sailed to Cyprus."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.5","order":"03.07.013.13263"},["b","5"],"And when they were at Salamis, they preached the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews: and they had also John to",["i","their"],"minister."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.6","order":"03.07.013.13264"},["b","6"],"And when they had gone through the isle unto Paphos, they found a certain",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_6a"},"sorcerer"],", a false prophet, a Jew, whose name",["i","was"],"Bar-jesus:"],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.7","order":"03.07.013.13265"},["b","7"],"Which was with the deputy of the country, Sergius Paulus, a",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_7a"},"prudent"],"man; who called for Barnabas and Saul, and desired to hear the word of God."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.8","order":"03.07.013.13266"},["b","8"],"But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name by interpretation) withstood them, seeking to turn away the deputy from the faith."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.9","order":"03.07.013.13267"},["b","9"],"Then Saul, (who also",["i","is called"],"Paul,) filled with the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_9a"},"Holy Ghost"],", set his eyes on him,"],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.10","order":"03.07.013.13268"},["b","10"],"And said, O full of all subtilty and all mischief,",["i","thou"],["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_10a"},"child"],"of the devil,",["i","thou"],["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_10b"},"enemy"],"of all",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_10c"},"righteousness"],", wilt thou not cease to pervert the right ways of the Lord?"],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.11","order":"03.07.013.13269"},["b","11"],"And now, behold, the hand of the Lord",["i","is"],"upon thee, and thou",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"shalt"],"be",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_11b"},"blind"],", not seeing the sun for a season. And immediately there fell on him a mist and a darkness; and he went about seeking some to lead him by the hand."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.12","order":"03.07.013.13270"},["b","12"],"Then the deputy, when he saw what was done, believed, being astonished at the doctrine of the Lord."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.13","order":"03.07.013.13271"},["b","13"],"Now when Paul and his company loosed from Paphos, they came to Perga in Pamphylia: and",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"John"],"departing from them returned to Jerusalem."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.14","order":"03.07.013.13272"},["b","14"],"¶But when they departed from Perga, they came to Antioch in Pisidia, and went into the synagogue on the sabbath day, and sat down."],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.15","order":"03.07.013.13273"},["b","15"],"And after the reading of the law and the prophets the rulers of the synagogue sent unto them, saying,",["i","Ye"],"men",["i","and"],"brethren, if ye have any word of exhortation for the people, say on."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.16","order":"03.07.013.13274"},["b","16"],"Then Paul stood up, and beckoning with",["i","his"],"hand said, Men of Israel, and ye that",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_16a"},"fear"],"God, give audience."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.17","order":"03.07.013.13275"},["b","17"],"The God of this people of Israel chose our fathers, and exalted the people when they dwelt as",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_17a"},"strangers"],"in the land of Egypt, and with an high arm brought he them out of it."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.18","order":"03.07.013.13276"},["b","18"],"And about the time of forty years suffered he their manners in the wilderness."],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.19","order":"03.07.013.13277"},["b","19"],"And when he had",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_19a"},"destroyed"],"seven nations in the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_19b"},"land of Chanaan"],", he divided their land to them by lot."],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.20","order":"03.07.013.13278"},["b","20"],"And after that he gave",["i","unto them"],"judges about the space of four hundred and fifty years, until Samuel the prophet."],["div",{"id":"21","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.21","order":"03.07.013.13279"},["b","21"],"And afterward they desired a king: and God gave unto them Saul the son of Cis, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, by the space of forty years."],["div",{"id":"22","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.22","order":"03.07.013.13280"},["b","22"],"And when he had removed him, he raised up unto them David to be their king; to whom also he gave testimony, and said, I have found David the",["i","son"],"of Jesse, a man after mine own",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_22a"},"heart"],", which shall fulfil all my will."],["div",{"id":"23","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.23","order":"03.07.013.13281"},["b","23"],"Of this man’s",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_23a"},"seed"],"hath God according to",["i","his"],["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_23b"},"promise"],"raised unto Israel a",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_23c"},"Saviour"],", Jesus:"],["div",{"id":"24","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.24","order":"03.07.013.13282"},["b","24"],"When John had first preached before his coming the baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel."],["div",{"id":"25","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.25","order":"03.07.013.13283"},["b","25"],"And as John fulfilled his course, he said, Whom think ye that I am? I am not",["i","he."],"But, behold, there cometh one after me, whose shoes of",["i","his"],"feet I am not worthy to loose."],["div",{"id":"26","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.26","order":"03.07.013.13284"},["b","26"],"Men",["i","and"],"brethren, children of the stock of",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_26a"},"Abraham"],", and whosoever among you feareth God, to you is the word of this salvation sent."],["div",{"id":"27","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.27","order":"03.07.013.13285"},["b","27"],"For they that dwell at Jerusalem, and their rulers, because they knew him not, nor yet the voices of the prophets which are read every sabbath day, they have fulfilled",["i","them"],"in condemning",["i","him."]],["div",{"id":"28","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.28","order":"03.07.013.13286"},["b","28"],"And though they found no cause of death",["i","in him,"],"yet desired they Pilate that he should be",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_28a"},"slain"],"."],["div",{"id":"29","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.29","order":"03.07.013.13287"},["b","29"],"And when they had fulfilled all that was written of him, they took",["i","him"],"down from the tree, and laid",["i","him"],"in a sepulchre."],["div",{"id":"30","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.30","order":"03.07.013.13288"},["b","30"],"But God raised him from the dead:"],["div",{"id":"31","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.31","order":"03.07.013.13289"},["b","31"],"And he was",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_31a"},"seen"],"many days of them which came up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem, who are his",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_31b"},"witnesses"],"unto the people."],["div",{"id":"32","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.32","order":"03.07.013.13290"},["b","32"],"And we declare unto you glad tidings, how that the promise which was made unto the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_32a"},"fathers"],","],["div",{"id":"33","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.33","order":"03.07.013.13291"},["b","33"],"God hath fulfilled the same unto us their children, in that he hath raised up Jesus again; as it is also written in the second psalm, Thou art my",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_33a"},"Son"],", this day have I begotten thee."],["div",{"id":"34","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.34","order":"03.07.013.13292"},["b","34"],"And as concerning that he raised him up from the dead,",["i","now"],"no more to return to corruption, he said on this wise, I will give you the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_34a"},"sure"],"mercies of David."],["div",{"id":"35","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.35","order":"03.07.013.13293"},["b","35"],"Wherefore he saith also in another",["i","psalm,"],"Thou shalt not suffer thine Holy One to see corruption."],["div",{"id":"36","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.36","order":"03.07.013.13294"},["b","36"],"For David, after he had served his own generation by the will of God, fell on sleep, and was laid unto his fathers, and saw corruption:"],["div",{"id":"37","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.37","order":"03.07.013.13295"},["b","37"],"But he, whom God",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_37a"},"raised"],"again, saw no",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_37b"},"corruption"],"."],["div",{"id":"38","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.38","order":"03.07.013.13296"},["b","38"],"¶Be it known unto you therefore, men",["i","and"],"brethren, that through this man is preached unto you the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_38a"},"forgiveness"],"of sins:"],["div",{"id":"39","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.39","order":"03.07.013.13297"},["b","39"],"And by him all that believe are",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_39a"},"justified"],"from all things, from which ye could not be",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_39b"},"justified"],"by the",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_39c"},"law"],"of Moses."],["div",{"id":"40","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.40","order":"03.07.013.13298"},["b","40"],"Beware therefore, lest that come upon you, which is spoken of in the prophets;"],["div",{"id":"41","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.41","order":"03.07.013.13299"},["b","41"],"Behold, ye despisers, and wonder, and perish: for I work a work in your days, a",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_41a"},"work"],"which ye shall in no wise believe, though a man declare it unto you."],["div",{"id":"42","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.42","order":"03.07.013.13300"},["b","42"],"And when the Jews were gone out of the synagogue, the Gentiles besought that these words might be preached to them the next",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_42a"},"sabbath"],"."],["div",{"id":"43","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.43","order":"03.07.013.13301"},["b","43"],"Now when the congregation was broken up, many of the Jews and religious",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_43a"},"proselytes"],"followed Paul and Barnabas: who, speaking to them, persuaded them to continue in the grace of God."],["div",{"id":"44","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.44","order":"03.07.013.13302"},["b","44"],"¶And the next sabbath day came almost the whole city together to hear the word of God."],["div",{"id":"45","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.45","order":"03.07.013.13303"},["b","45"],"But when the Jews saw the multitudes, they were filled with",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_45a"},"envy"],", and spake",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_45b"},"against"],"those things which were spoken by Paul, contradicting and",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_45c"},"blaspheming"],"."],["div",{"id":"46","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.46","order":"03.07.013.13304"},["b","46"],"Then Paul and Barnabas waxed bold, and said, It was necessary that the word of God should first have been spoken to you: but seeing ye put it from you, and judge yourselves unworthy of everlasting life, lo, we turn to the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_46a"},"Gentiles"],"."],["div",{"id":"47","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.47","order":"03.07.013.13305"},["b","47"],"For so hath the Lord commanded us,",["i","saying,"],"I have set thee to be a",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_47a"},"light"],"of the Gentiles, that thou shouldest be for",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_47b"},"salvation"],"unto the ends of the earth."],["div",{"id":"48","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.48","order":"03.07.013.13306"},["b","48"],"And when the Gentiles heard this, they were glad, and glorified the word of the Lord:",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_48a"},"and"],"as many as were ordained to eternal life believed."],["div",{"id":"49","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.49","order":"03.07.013.13307"},["b","49"],"And the word of the Lord was",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_49a"},"published"],"throughout all the region."],["div",{"id":"50","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.50","order":"03.07.013.13308"},["b","50"],"But the Jews",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_50a"},"stirred up"],"the devout and honourable",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_50b"},"women"],", and the chief men of the city, and raised",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_50c"},"persecution"],"against Paul and Barnabas, and expelled them out of their coasts."],["div",{"id":"51","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.51","order":"03.07.013.13309"},["b","51"],"But they shook off the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_51a"},"dust"],"of their feet against them, and came unto Iconium."],["div",{"id":"52","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.52","order":"03.07.013.13310"},["b","52"],"And the disciples were filled with joy, and with the Holy Ghost."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.1a","order":"03.07.013.13311"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/11.27"},"Acts 11:27"],".",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/church-organization"},"TG Church Organization"],"."],["div",{"id":"2a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.2a","order":"03.07.013.13313"},["b","2a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/5.35"},"Luke 5:35"],".",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/fast-fasting"},"TG Fast, Fasting"],"."],["div",{"id":"2b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.2b","order":"03.07.013.13315"},["b","2b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/holy-ghost-gifts-of"},"TG Holy Ghost, Gifts of"],"."],["div",{"id":"2c","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.2c","order":"03.07.013.13317"},["b","2c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/setting-apart"},"TG Setting Apart"],"."],["div",{"id":"2d","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.2d","order":"03.07.013.13319"},["b","2d"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/called-of-god"},"TG Called of God"],"."],["div",{"id":"3a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.3a","order":"03.07.013.13321"},["b","3a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/authority"},"TG Authority"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/priesthood-authority"},"Priesthood, Authority"],"."],["div",{"id":"3b","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.3b","order":"03.07.013.13323"},["b","3b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/hands-laying-on-of"},"TG Hands, Laying on of"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/priesthood-ordination"},"Priesthood, Ordination"],"."],["div",{"id":"6a","uri":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13.6a","order":"0